// Managed by Ansible (roles/headscale). HuJSON (JSON + comments/trailing commas).
//
// Permissive start: every tailnet member can reach every other member. This is
// a single-operator household tailnet, so we open it up first and tighten later
// (see notes/headscale_mesh_redesign.md "ACL policy"). Kept deliberately free of
// tagOwners/group references so the policy is valid on a fresh instance with no
// users yet -- a policy that names a non-existent owner makes headscale refuse
// to load it. Subnet routes and exit nodes are approved explicitly via
// `headscale nodes approve-routes` (delegated from the tailscale role), not via
// autoApprovers (which would need the tagOwners we deliberately omit here).
{
  "acls": [
    {
      "action": "accept",
      "src": ["*"],
      "dst": ["*:*"],
    },
  ],
}
